<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Clarification</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Wrex">Wrex</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:44 p.m. 16/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Clarification<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1492" TARGET=_self>Here are some of my thoughts Geig.. you can't expect friends to roleplay non stop</A> (Tarquin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Just out of curiousity, who would group with an insane homicidal gnome necro? Your friends that you group with do. So, obviously, you only roleplay, and this is important, as a matter of convenience. So, therefore, you have very little of the inherent hinderences of the profession you are playing. For example, if you want to sell something, you give it to one of your friends, and they sell it for you. I'm not saying there is nothing wrong with this. But what it DOES do is give you a work-around to many of the disadvantages of the profession.

<P>I personally have no problem with your style of play. I just don't like hearing you rationalize how your play can be fun to others.
<P>If you see a situation where you can obviously defeat a weakened or outnumbered opponent, you take advantage of it. There is nothing wrong with this either, except when you whine when the same happens to you.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
